<p><b>Online advertising</b> is a form of <a href="/wiki/Promotion" title="Promotion">promotion</a> that uses the <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a> and <a href="/wiki/World_Wide_Web" title="World Wide Web">World Wide Web</a> for the expressed purpose of delivering <a href="/wiki/Marketing" title="Marketing">marketing</a> messages to attract customers. Examples of online advertising include contextual ads on <a href="/wiki/Search_engine_results_page" title="Search engine results page">search engine results pages</a>, <a href="/wiki/Banner_ad" title="Banner ad" class="mw-redirect">banner ads</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rich_Media" title="Rich Media" class="mw-redirect">Rich Media</a> Ads, <a href="/wiki/Social_network_advertising" title="Social network advertising">Social network advertising</a>, <a href="/wiki/Online_classified_advertising" title="Online classified advertising" class="mw-redirect">online classified advertising</a>, <a href="/wiki/Advertising_network" title="Advertising network">advertising networks</a> and <a href="/wiki/E-mail_marketing" title="E-mail marketing">e-mail marketing</a>, including <a href="/wiki/E-mail_spam" title="E-mail spam">e-mail spam</a>.</p>
<p>Online video directories for brands are a good example of interactive advertising. These directories complement television advertising and allow the viewer to view the commercials of a number of brands. If the advertiser has opted for a response feature, the viewer may then choose to visit the brand’s website, or interact with the advertiser through other touch points such as email, chat or phone. Response to brand communication is instantaneous, and conversion to business is very high. This is because in contrast to conventional forms of interruptive advertising, the viewer has actually chosen to see the commercial.</p>
